fields.value: Census of population and housing, 1970 summary statistic file 2

dsDescriptionValue.value:
"The data files include 93 tables containing 3,500 population and housing data cells. The subject matter is identical for each of the files. Population items that are cross-tabulated include single years of age, race, sex, household relationship, and family type. Housing items that are cross-tabulated include persons in unit, tenure and race of head, population in units by selected age classes, plumbing facilities, tenure, race of head, etc. This file is also known as ""Second Count."""

The two files have variables in geography. In File A summaries are given for all census tracts, including those not in SMSA's. In File B summaries are provided by States, SMSA's and their component counties, urbanized areas, counties, minor civil divisions (or census county divisions), and places of 1,000 or more inhabitants.

Data contained in the files pertain to the date of the census, April 1, 1970
